Events.html: 338 BC – A Macedonian army led by Philip II defeated the combined forces of Athens and Thebes in the Battle of Chaeronea, securing Macedonian hegemony in Greece and the Aegean.
Events.text: A Macedonian army led by Philip II defeated the combined forces of Athens and Thebes in the Battle of Chaeronea, securing Macedonian hegemony in Greece and the Aegean.

Events.html: 216 BC – Second Punic War: Battle of Cannae – The Carthaginian army led by Hannibal defeats a numerically superior Roman army under command of consuls Lucius Aemilius Paullus and Gaius Terentius Varro.
Events.text: Second Punic War: Battle of Cannae – The Carthaginian army led by Hannibal defeats a numerically superior Roman army under command of consuls Lucius Aemilius Paullus and Gaius Terentius Varro.

Events.html: 461 – Majorian is arrested near Tortona (Northern Italy) and deposed by the Suebian general Ricimer as puppet emperor.
Events.text: Majorian is arrested near Tortona (Northern Italy) and deposed by the Suebian general Ricimer as puppet emperor.

Events.html: 1343 – Olivier de Clisson is found guilty of treason and beheaded at Les Halles in Paris. As a result, his wife, Jeanne de Clisson, sold their holding, bought a fleet of ships, and took to the sea as a pirate to seek revenge against the French King and nobility.
Events.text: Olivier de Clisson is found guilty of treason and beheaded at Les Halles in Paris. As a result, his wife, Jeanne de Clisson, sold their holding, bought a fleet of ships, and took to the sea as a pirate to seek revenge against the French King and nobility.

Events.html: 1377 – Russian troops are defeated in the Battle on Pyana River.
Events.text: Russian troops are defeated in the Battle on Pyana River.

Events.html: 1610 – Henry Hudson sails into what is now known as Hudson Bay thinking he had made it through the Northwest Passage and reached the Pacific Ocean.
Events.text: Henry Hudson sails into what is now known as Hudson Bay thinking he had made it through the Northwest Passage and reached the Pacific Ocean.

Events.html: 1776 – The signing of the United States Declaration of Independence took place.
Events.text: The signing of the United States Declaration of Independence took place.

Events.html: 1790 – The first United States Census is conducted.
Events.text: The first United States Census is conducted.

Events.html: 1798 – French Revolutionary Wars: the Battle of the Nile concludes in a British victory.
Events.text: French Revolutionary Wars: the Battle of the Nile concludes in a British victory.

Events.html: 1830 – Charles X of France abdicates the throne in favor of his grandson Henri.
Events.text: Charles X of France abdicates the throne in favor of his grandson Henri.

Events.html: 1869 – Japan's samurai, farmer, artisan, merchant class system (Shinōkōshō) is abolished as part of the Meiji Restoration reforms. (Traditional Japanese date: June 25, 1869).
Events.text: Japan's samurai, farmer, artisan, merchant class system (Shinōkōshō) is abolished as part of the Meiji Restoration reforms. (Traditional Japanese date: June 25, 1869).

Events.html: 1870 – Tower Subway, the world's first underground tube railway, opens in London, England, United Kingdom.
Events.text: Tower Subway, the world's first underground tube railway, opens in London, England, United Kingdom.

Events.html: 1873 – The Clay Street Hill Railroad begins operating the first cable car in San Francisco's famous cable car system.
Events.text: The Clay Street Hill Railroad begins operating the first cable car in San Francisco's famous cable car system.

Events.html: 1897 – Anglo-Afghan War: The Siege of Malakand ends when a relief column is able to reach the British garrison in the Malakand states adjacent to India's North West Frontier Province.
Events.text: Anglo-Afghan War: The Siege of Malakand ends when a relief column is able to reach the British garrison in the Malakand states adjacent to India's North West Frontier Province.

Events.html: 1903 – Fall of the Ottoman Empire: an unsuccessful uprising led by the Internal Macedonian Revolutionary Organization against Ottoman Turkey, also known as the Ilinden–Preobrazhenie Uprising, takes place.
Events.text: Fall of the Ottoman Empire: an unsuccessful uprising led by the Internal Macedonian Revolutionary Organization against Ottoman Turkey, also known as the Ilinden–Preobrazhenie Uprising, takes place.

Events.html: 1916 – World War I: Austrian sabotage causes the sinking of the Italian battleship Leonardo da Vinci in Taranto.
Events.text: World War I: Austrian sabotage causes the sinking of the Italian battleship Leonardo da Vinci in Taranto.

Events.html: 1918 – Japan announces that it is deploying troops to Siberia in the aftermath of World War I.
Events.text: Japan announces that it is deploying troops to Siberia in the aftermath of World War I.

Events.html: 1918 – The first general strike in Canadian history takes place in Vancouver.

Events.html: 1922 – A typhoon hits Shantou, Republic of China killing more than 50,000 people.

Events.html: 1932 – The positron (antiparticle of the electron) is discovered by Carl D. Anderson.

Events.html: 1934 – Gleichschaltung: Adolf Hitler becomes Führer of Germany following the death of President Paul von Hindenburg.

Events.html: 1937 – The Marihuana Tax Act of 1937 is passed in America, the effect of which is to render marijuana and all its by-products illegal.

Events.html: 1939 – Albert Einstein and Leó Szilárd write a letter to Franklin D. Roosevelt, urging him to begin the Manhattan Project to develop a nuclear weapon.

Events.html: 1943 – Rebellion in the Nazi death camp of Treblinka.
Events.text: Rebellion in the Nazi death camp of Treblinka.

Events.html: 1943 – World War II: the Motor Torpedo Boat PT-109 is rammed by the Japanese destroyer Amagiri and sinks. Lt. John F. Kennedy, future U.S. President, saves all but two of his crew.

Events.html: 1944 – ASNOM: birth of the Socialist Republic of Macedonia, celebrated as Day of the Republic in the Republic of Macedonia.

Events.html: 1944 – World War II: The largest trade convoy of the world wars arrives safely in the Western Approaches.

Events.html: 1947 – A British South American Airways Avro Lancastrian airliner crashes into a mountain during a flight from Buenos Aires, Argentina to Santiago, Chile. The wreckage would not be found for over 50 years.

Events.html: 1964 – Vietnam War: Gulf of Tonkin incident – North Vietnamese gunboats allegedly fire on the U.S. destroyer USS Maddox.

Events.html: 1968 – An earthquake hits Casiguran, Aurora, Philippines killing more than 270 people and wounding 261.
